summary: This document is a U.S. Department of Justice foreign travel authorization questionnaire for an Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) from the Southern District of New York (SDNY) traveling to Stockholm, Sweden in February 2020. The purpose of the trip is to interview and debrief a witness (referred to as 'Jane Doe, Swedish') in the ongoing, sensitive investigation into Jeffrey Epstein, with Ghislaine Maxwell identified as a subject.

keyFacts: The travel is for an Assistant U.S. Attorney from SDNY to interview a Swedish witness ('Jane Doe') in Stockholm in February 2020 as part of the ongoing investigation into Jeffrey Epstein (USAO # 2018R01618).
The investigation is described as 'ongoing and very sensitive,' and Ghislaine Maxwell is explicitly named as a subject of the investigation.
The travel itinerary shows a round trip from New York (JFK) to Stockholm via London Heathrow from February 3 to February 6, 2020, with lodging at the Sheraton Stockholm Hotel.
The questionnaire indicates that foreign authorities have cleared the visit and are prepared to cooperate, though no specific foreign contacts are named.
The traveler's security clearance is listed as Top Secret, and they have completed required High Threat Security Overseas Seminar training.
